Title: Be careful with ToListAsync and ToArrayAsync in Entity Framework Core
Description: Entity Framework has two methods for converting a query to a list or an array: ToListAsync and ToArrayAsync. Of course there is also the sync version of these methods: ToList and ToArray. And sometimes, you should use the latter one!

Title: Mastering EF Core: Scaffold DB Context from Existing Database in .NET
Description:
Unlock the power of Database First approach in Entity Framework Core with this comprehensive step-by-step tutorial! Learn how to create an EF Core model by scaffolding a DB context from an existing database. Perfect for C# developers working with Entity Framework Core and looking to enhance their database integration skills. In this video, you'll discover:

• How to set up your environment for Database First approach
• Implementing scaffold commands to generate your DB context
• Customizing and optimizing the generated models
• Best practices for working with existing databases in EF Core

Whether you're new to EF Core or an experienced developer, this guide will help you seamlessly integrate existing databases into your .NET applications. Boost your skills in database programming, ASP.NET Core, and C# development.

Title: I Waited 10 Billion Cycles and All I Got Was This Loading Screen
Description: Modern hardware is unbelievably fast. The M1 Max that I’m writing this article on runs at 3.2GHz. That is 3.2 BILLION clock cycles per second. Yet, Microsoft Teams takes 3 seconds to open a link, and I refuse to believe it takes 9.6 BILLION clock cycles to open a link. Obviously, that’s an over-simplification, but the point stands: how is it that hardware gets faster, but the applications we use only get slower?

Title: Re-ranking search results on the client side
Description:
By many measures, Mwmbl is doing great. We have indexed over half a billion pages, we have over 4,000 registered users, and over 30,000 curations from those users. Our volunteers are crawling around 5 million pages a day.
But the score that I care about most right now is NDCG. This measures the quality of our search results against a “gold standard” which is just Bing search results for the same query.
